## Description {#details}

Utility class that carries the DWARF compile/type unit and the debug info entry in an object.

When accessing information from a debug info entry we always need to DWARF compile/type unit in order to extract the info correctly as some information is relative to the compile/type unit. Prior to this class the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dwarfunit">DWARFUnit</a> and the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dwarfdebuginfoentry">DWARFDebugInfoEntry</a> was passed around separately and there was the possibility for error if the wrong <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dwarfunit">DWARFUnit</a> was used to extract a unit relative offset. This class helps to ensure that this doesn&#39;t happen and also simplifies the attribute extraction calls by not having to specify the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dwarfunit">DWARFUnit</a> for each call.

Definition at line 42 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/debuginfo/include/llvm/debuginfo/dwarf/dwarfdie-h">DWARFDie.h</a>.

### getHighPC() {#a75a8f3e9af7915e4b0b10f9e17de63ca}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>std::optional&lt; uint64&#95;t &gt; DWARFDie::getHighPC (uint64&#95;t LowPC) const</>}>
Get the DW&#95;AT&#95;high&#95;pc attribute value as an address.

In DWARF version 4 and later the high PC can be encoded as an offset from the DW&#95;AT&#95;low&#95;pc. This function takes care of extracting the value as an address or offset and adds it to the low PC if needed and returns the value as an optional in case the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/die">DIE</a> doesn&#39;t have a DW&#95;AT&#95;high&#95;pc attribute.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="LowPC">the low PC that might be needed to calculate the high PC.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

<SectionUser title="Returns">
an optional address value for the attribute.
</SectionUser>
